<DATE>07/01/2008</DATE>
<AUTHOR>Daniel</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>My wife and I have 11,000 miles on ours and we love it. The people who complain about the gas mileage are the same people you see gunning off the line, only having to slam on the brakes in 100 yards. We are averaging about 27 MPG city, and 34 MPG highway, with A/C. This should be an option for everyone who is looking at a 3 series BMW. No, the fit and finish isn't as nice, and the engine isn't as peppy, but it is an amazing car with a less expensive starting piont.</TEXT>
<FAVORITE>Look, on board computer, T-Tec seats.</FAVORITE>
